      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The standard industry methods for auditing inventory discrepancies often involve manual counts, cycle counting, and physical audits. Cycle counting involves selecting a random subset of items to count regularly to identify errors in storage and retrieval. Physical audits involve conducting a full count of the entire warehouse to verify the accuracy of the system data. Another method is the ABC analysis, where high-value items are counted more frequently.",
