      "content": "While emotional and psychological factors can play a role in unexplained shrinkage, also consider external factors such as supplier errors, damage during transportation, or even pest activity. Look for patterns in the types of items being affected, and consider if any products are more prone to being misplaced. Additionally, examine your warehouse inventory turnover, as items that frequently get moved or replaced may be more likely to experience unexplained shortages.",
